defaultThis comprehensive systematic review concluded that there was strong scientific evidence (Grade A) - including 4 good quality RCTs involving 933 participants - to support the use of pelargonium for acute bronchitis and good scientific evidence (Grade B) for the its use in acute 
defaultpharyngitis
default and the common cold. No serious toxic effects have been observed in any trial relating to pelargonium.
defaultPelargonium has exhibited a marked antibacterial action against a wide range of pathogenic bacteria.
