default129 patients with RUTIs were randomised to active herbal or placebo treatment for 90 days. The primary outcome was the number of laboratory confirmed urinary tract infections.
default The per protocol mean number of recurrent UTIs in the 
defaultstudy period was 0.43 versus 0.77 for the placebo group. This result is statistically significant (p = 0.035). A total of 36 patients in the test group and 37 patients in the placebo group reported adverse events. Two serious adverse events were reported in the placebo group and one serious adverse event in the treatment group (not associated with the study medication).
defaultThis herbal product appears to be effective and safe as a prophylaxis for RUTIs.
defaultMustard oils (including 
defaultisothiocyanates
default) found in these two herbs have been shown to have a broad spectrum antibacterial action.
