defaultanalysis.)
defaultA randomised control trial of a complex Chinese herbal medicine (San Ling 
defaultJie
default Du Tang) in the treatment of women with recurrent lower urinary tract infections (RUTIs)
defaultHuang MJ. (2007). 
defaultHubei J. of Traditional Chinese Medicine
default;29:38-9.
default300 women were randomised in a 2:1 ratio to the Chinese herbal remedy or an antibiotic. Treatment was administered for 7 days with a 6 month follow up. 
default79.5% of the herbal group reported no infection in the follow up period compared with 49% in the antibiotic group. This was statistically significant (p&lt;0.05).
defaultSeveral of the included herbs, such as tree peony bark (
defaultPaeonia
